if i download chatgpt desktop, will it be able to edit my code in desktop ?

Short answer: Yes, but not directly.
ChatGPT Desktop can help edit your code, but it cannot automatically change files on your computer unless you copy/paste or use an editor integration.

Here is how it actually works.

✅ What ChatGPT Desktop CAN do
Read code you paste

Rewrite code

Fix errors

Generate new files

Help debug

Help with Python / Streamlit / React / Django / etc.

You copy code from your editor → paste here → I edit → you paste back.

This is how most developers use it.

✅ What ChatGPT Desktop CANNOT do (by default)
❌ Cannot open your folders automatically
❌ Cannot edit files directly on your PC
❌ Cannot save changes to your project
❌ Cannot control VS Code automatically

For security reasons.

✅ Best setup (recommended for you)
Use:

VS Code

ChatGPT Desktop

GitHub

Workflow:

Open code in VS Code

Copy code → paste in ChatGPT

I fix / improve

Paste back

Run

This is normal developer workflow.

✅ If you want automatic editing (advanced)
Possible with:

VS Code extensions

Copilot

Cursor AI

ChatGPT API tools

Best tool right now for auto-edit:

👉 Cursor IDE
👉 VSCode + Copilot
👉 ChatGPT + plugins (limited)

✅ My recommendation for you
Use:

VS Code + ChatGPT + Streamlit
Perfect for dashboard project.

