Unable to deploy
The app’s code is not connected to a remote GitHub repository. To deploy on Streamlit Community Cloud, please put your code in a GitHub repository and publish the current branch. Read more in our documentation.

That error means your code is only on your computer right now. Streamlit Cloud can deploy only from a GitHub repo, not from a local folder.

Do this:

1) Create a GitHub repo
On GitHub, click New repository and create one, for example nac-dashboard.

2) Put your project in that repo
In your project folder, run these commands in terminal:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/nac-dashboard.git
git push -u origin main
Replace:

https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/nac-dashboard.git
with your actual repo URL.

3) Confirm files are on GitHub
Open your repo in browser and make sure these are there:

app.py

requirements.txt

your data files

.gitignore

4) Deploy again on Streamlit Cloud
Go back to Streamlit Community Cloud, select that repo, choose branch main, and set the main file path to:

app.py
If Git says authentication failed, the easiest path is to upload the files directly on GitHub website instead of terminal:

open the new repo

click upload files

drag all project files

commit changes

Then deploy from Streamlit.

If you want, send me the exact step where you got stuck and I’ll walk you through it.


(base) asheshlalshrestha@Asheshs-MacBook-Pro-2 NAC-Dashboard % git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/nac-dashboard.git
error: remote origin already exists.

This error is normal 👍
It means you already added a remote once, so Git is not allowing you to add it again.

We just need to change the remote URL, not add a new one.

✅ Step 1 — Check current remote
Run:

git remote -v
You will see something like:

origin  https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/old-repo.git (fetch)
origin  https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/old-repo.git (push)
✅ Step 2 — Replace with correct repo URL
Run:

git remote set-url origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/nac-dashboard.git
Replace with your real repo link.

Example:

git remote set-url origin https://github.com/ashesh123/nac-dashboard.git
✅ Step 3 — Push again
git push -u origin main
If branch error:

git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
✅ Step 4 — Check GitHub
Open repo in browser
You should see files.

If files are there → Streamlit will work.

✅ Step 5 — Deploy again
Go to Streamlit Cloud

Select:

repo: nac-dashboard
branch: main
file: app.py
Deploy.

✅ If you want, paste this output
Run:

git remote -v
git branch
