how long is this deployed for

Good question. Since you used Streamlit Community Cloud (free), the deployment does not expire, but there are some rules.

✅ How long will it stay deployed?
It stays online forever as long as:

The GitHub repo exists

You don’t delete the app from Streamlit

You don’t violate limits

So your link

https://nac-dashboard.streamlit.app/
can stay live for months or years.

⚠️ Free plan limits
1. App sleeps if not used
If nobody opens the app for some time, it goes to sleep.

When someone opens it again:

It restarts automatically

Takes ~5–20 seconds

This is normal.

2. Limited resources
Free plan has limits:

RAM limit

CPU limit

Storage limit

Only a few apps allowed

But your dashboard is small → perfectly fine.

3. If repo is deleted → app stops
If you delete GitHub repo → deployment breaks.

✅ When will it stop working?
Only if:

You delete repo

You delete app in Streamlit

You exceed limits

Streamlit removes inactive apps (rare)

Otherwise → stays live.

✅ If you want permanent / professional hosting
Better options:

Render

Railway

AWS

Azure

Vercel (for frontend)

HuggingFace Spaces

I can also show pro hosting setup if you want.


do I have to run the app locally to make it work ?

No — you do NOT need to run the app locally anymore. ✅

Since you deployed on Streamlit Community Cloud, the app is now running on Streamlit’s servers, not your laptop.

Your link

https://nac-dashboard.streamlit.app/
will work even if:

your laptop is off

you close VS Code

you shut down terminal

you restart your computer

So your friend can open it anytime.

✅ When do you need to run locally?
Only when you want to:

change code

add new charts

fix bugs

update data

test before pushing

Workflow now is:

Edit code locally

Push to GitHub

Streamlit auto-deploys

Link updates automatically

You do NOT need to run streamlit locally for others to see it.

✅ Example workflow
Edit code:

app.py
Then:

git add .
git commit -m "update dashboard"
git push
Streamlit will redeploy automatically.

✅ Important
Local run = for development
Streamlit Cloud = for sharing

You are now in cloud mode, so you are good.



