About the pictures not loading: that usually happens because the app is trying to show external image URLs and Streamlit cannot fetch them reliably due to hotlink restrictions, URL changes, or remote blocking. The safest fix is to use local image files inside your repo instead of web links.

Do this:

Save 2 images into your project folder, for example:

images/nepal_airlines_plane.jpg

images/drukair_plane.jpg

In app.py, replace URL-based image code with:

from pathlib import Path
import streamlit as st

BASE_DIR = Path(__file__).parent

nepal_img = BASE_DIR / "images" / "nepal_airlines_plane.jpg"
druk_img = BASE_DIR / "images" / "drukair_plane.jpg"

col1, col2 = st.columns(2)
with col1:
    st.image(str(nepal_img), caption="Nepal Airlines", use_container_width=True)
with col2:
    st.image(str(druk_img), caption="Druk Air", use_container_width=True)
Then push again:

git add .
git commit -m "fix local plane images"
git push
