give me gitignore as well

Use this .gitignore for your Streamlit / Python dashboard project.
This will ignore venv, cache, images temp, and system files.

Create file:

touch .gitignore
Then open .gitignore and paste this:

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
*.sqlite3

# Virtual environment
venv/
.env/
.venv/
env/

# Streamlit cache
.streamlit/

# VS Code
.vscode/

# Mac
.DS_Store

# Windows
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log

# Jupyter
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Build
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/

# Secrets
.env
.env.local

# Temporary
*.tmp
*.bak

# Zip files
*.zip

# Python cache folders
.cache/

# pytest
.pytest_cache/

# mypy
.mypy_cache/

# images generated (optional)
# comment this if you want images tracked
# images/

# data temp files
*.csv~
*.json~
✅ Important for your project
DO NOT ignore these:

app.py
requirements.txt
data/
images/
because Streamlit needs them.

✅ After creating .gitignore
Run:

git add .
git commit -m "add gitignore"
git push
✅ If you want professional data-science gitignore
Say:

advanced gitignore for streamlit



